race.comment: THE CRIMSON PIRATE (1) showed plenty of talent in his debut campaign but got a long way off the leader/winner last start when the race favourite. He was solid to the line there and the rise in trip looks ideal. Love that the ear muffs come off and he looks the one to beat. AUSSIE REACTOR (2) has flown home in his past two outings, beaten 0.4L at this track and trip 11 days ago. The horse he finished behind there won at Ascot on Tuesday. Can sit much closer from the barrier this time around and put his best foot forward. ADMIRE ASTRA (7) just missed as favourite on debut before flying home over this track and trip last time out. Blinkers go on now as she comes here on the quick turnaround. Pike remains in the saddle however and she's expected to be in the finish again. BONDI LIFESAVER (3) comes through the same race as THE CRIMSON PIRATE and has claims. TANUNDA (5) creates interest on debut.
